ing shortcut</li><li> By pressing the preview button</li></ul><h4 id="using-shortcut"> Using shortcut</h4><p> If you want to use the shortcut, all you have to do is press the <code>Ctrl + K</code> and then press the <code>V</code> key and it will bring the preview panel: </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card"><img src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/Use-shortcut-to-get-preview-panel-to-preview-markdown-in-vs-code.gif" class="kg-image" alt="How to Preview Markdown in Visual Studio Code" loading="lazy" width="1424" height="554" srcset="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/Use-shortcut-to-get-preview-panel-to-preview-markdown-in-vs-code.gif 600w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w1000/2023/09/Use-shortcut-to-get-preview-panel-to-preview-markdown-in-vs-code.gif 1000w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/Use-shortcut-to-get-preview-panel-to-preview-markdown-in-vs-code.gif 1424w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"></figure><p> As you can see, it brings a preview panel to the right side of the current file.</p><h4 id="using-the-preview-button"> Using the preview button</h4><p> If you don&#39;t like the idea of using shortcuts for everything, there&#39;s a preview button available in VS Code by which you can bring the preview panel easily.</p><p> Here&#39;s where it is located at: </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card"><img src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/Preview-button-in-markdown-vs-code.png" class="kg-image" alt="How to Preview Markdown in Visual Studio Code" loading="lazy" width="1326" height="423" srcset="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/Preview-button-in-markdown-vs-code.png 600w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w1000/2023/09/Preview-button-in-markdown-vs-code.png 1000w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/Preview-button-in-markdown-vs-code.png 1326w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"></figure><p> When pressed, here&#39;s how it gets you a preview: </p><figure class="kg-car